0:16:31.26,000 --> 0:16:33,000
because it would be a kind of

424
0:16:33.26,000 --> 0:16:35,000
gastronomic Russian roulette.

425
0:16:35.26,000 --> 0:16:37,000
Sometimes you have a toxic bloom;

426
0:16:37.26,000 --> 0:16:39,000
sometimes you don't.

427
0:16:39.26,000 --> 0:16:41,000
That doesn't sell.

428
0:16:41.26,000 --> 0:16:43,000
The really scary things though

429
0:16:43.26,000 --> 0:16:46,000
are the physical, chemical,

430
0:16:46.26,000 --> 0:16:49,000
oceanographic things that are happening.

431
0:16:49.26,000 --> 0:16:52,000
As the surface of the ocean gets warmer,

432
0:16:52.26,000 --> 0:16:54,000
the water is lighter when it's warmer,

433
0:16:54.26,000 --> 0:16:56,000
it becomes harder and harder

434
0:16:56.26,000 --> 0:16:58,000
to turn the ocean over.

435
0:16:58.26,000 --> 0:17:,000
We say it becomes

436
0:17:00.26,000 --> 0:17:02,000
more strongly stratified.

437
0:17:02.26,000 --> 0:17:04,000
The consequence of that is that

438
0:17:04.26,000 --> 0:17:06,000
all those nutrients

439
0:17:06.26,000 --> 0:17:09,000
that fuel the great anchoveta fisheries,

440
0:17:09.26,000 --> 0:17:11,000
of the sardines of California

441
0:17:11.26,000 --> 0:17:14,000
or in Peru or whatever,

442
0:17:14.26,000 --> 0:17:16,000
those slow down

443
0:17:16.26,000 --> 0:17:18,000
and those fisheries collapse.

444
0:17:18.26,000 --> 0:17:2,000
And, at the same time,

445
0:17:20.26,000 --> 0:17:23,000
water from the surface, which is rich in oxygen,

446
0:17:23.26,000 --> 0:17:26,000
doesn't make it down

447
0:17:27.26,000 --> 0:17:3,000
and the ocean turns into a desert.

448
0:17:30.26,000 --> 0:17:32,000
So the question is: How are we all

449
0:17:32.26,000 --> 0:17:34,000
going to respond to this?

