0:17:34.26,000 --> 0:17:36,000
And we can do

451
0:17:36.26,000 --> 0:17:38,000
all sorts of things to fix it,

452
0:17:38.26,000 --> 0:17:4,000
but in the final analysis,

453
0:17:40.26,000 --> 0:17:42,000
the thing we really need to fix

454
0:17:42.26,000 --> 0:17:44,000
is ourselves.

455
0:17:44.26,000 --> 0:17:47,000
It's not about the fish; it's not about the pollution;

456
0:17:47.26,000 --> 0:17:49,000
it's not about the climate change.

457
0:17:49.26,000 --> 0:17:51,000
It's about us

458
0:17:51.26,000 --> 0:17:54,000
and our greed and our need for growth

459
0:17:54.26,000 --> 0:17:57,000
and our inability to imagine a world

460
0:17:57.26,000 --> 0:17:59,000
that is different from the selfish world

461
0:17:59.26,000 --> 0:18:01,000
we live in today.

462
0:18:01.26,000 --> 0:18:04,000
So the question is: Will we respond to this or not?

463
0:18:04.26,000 --> 0:18:06,000
I would say that the future of life

464
0:18:06.26,000 --> 0:18:08,000
and the dignity of human beings

465
0:18:08.26,000 --> 0:18:1,000
depends on our doing that.

466
0:18:10.26,000 --> 0:18:12,000
Thank you. (Applause)

